On 21 July, the SCAF announced that it would bar foreign monitors in the upcoming [[Egyptian parliamentary election, 2011|parliamentary election]] because of what it claimed was the preservation of Egyptian sovereingty<Ref>http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2011/07/2011720222415556480.html</ref>.

On 23 July, Thousands of protesters tried to march to the headquarters of Egypt's military junta when they were attacked by groups of men wielding knives, sticks, stones and [[Molotov cocktail|molotov cocktails]]<ref>http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2011/jul/24/egypt-protest-march-military-council</ref><ref>http://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFJOE76N01L20110724?sp=true</ref>. It was the second time in two days that crowds had tried to march to the headquarters <ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-14265772</ref> located in [[Heliopolis]].
